    "body": "I did a test with the node version from atom 1.2.0 and node had no trouble writing to my fuse directory, so the problem must be in electron.\n\nHow to repeat this problem in just a few minutes...\n- download http://sourceforge.net/projects/fuse/files/fuse-2.X/2.9.4/\n- `cd fuse-2*`  you will be in this fuze install dir for the rest of these instructions\n- `./configure --prefix=/usr`\n- `make`\n- `mkdir fuze-dir` to make a dir to mount the fuze file system on\n- `sshfs localhost:/$home fuze-dir` to mount `$home` on `fuze-dir`\n- `ls -al fuze-dir` to see mount worked and permissions correct\n- `atom fuze-dir` with any atom after 1.1.0 and see permissions error\n- `umount fuze-dir` when done \n\nBTW, I found sshfs when creating these instructions but it looks like a very useful tool in general.  It can mount any remote directory as a local one.\n"
