    "body": "(Copy from atom/atom issue  https://github.com/atom/atom/issues/9555).\n\nI have found out that the parents of fuse directories had 600 permissions instead of the usual 755.  This means that any other user wouldn't be able to list the directory I was trying to open with Atom.  But I am always logged in as root and I always start atom with root.  So I think this is the wrong behavior.  Atom shouldn't behave like a different user.  Also it didn't have this problem until after 1.1.0.\n\nIn any case I have fixed my problem by setting all dirs to 755.  So I have a workaround.  If anyone wants I'll file another issue about this anomalous behavior but I'm closing this one. \n"
